"Swingedouw D., Fichefet T., Huybrechts P., Goosse H., Driesschaert E., Loutre M.-F.","Antarctic ice-sheet melting provides negative feedbacks on future climate warming",2008,"Geophysical Research Letters","35","17", L17705,"","",,,10.1029/2008GL034410,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-57049169780&partnerID=40&md5=962ab85961c3375827027668c430d948","Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium; Department of Geography, Vrije Universiteit Brussel, Pleinlaan 2, B-1050 Brussels, Belgium","Swingedouw, D., Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium; Fichefet, T., Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium; Huybrechts, P., Department of Geography, Vrije Universiteit Brussel, Pleinlaan 2, B-1050 Brussels, Belgium; Goosse, H., Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium; Driesschaert, E., Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium; Loutre, M.-F., Institut d'Astronomie et de Géophysique Georges Lemaître, Université Catholique de Louvain, Chemin du Cyclotron 2, B-1348 Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium","We show by using a three-dimensional climate model, which includes a comprehensive representation of polar ice sheets, that on centennial to millennial time scales Antarctic Ice Sheet (AIS) can melt and moderate warming in the Southern Hemisphere, by up to 10°C regionally, in a 4 × CO2 scenario. This behaviour stems from the formation of a cold halocline in the Southern Ocean, which limits sea-ice cover retreat under global warming and increases surface albedo, reducing local surface warming. Furthermore, we show that AIS melting, by decreasing Antarctic Bottom Water formation, restrains the weakening of the Atlantic meridional overturning circulation, which is a new illustration of the effect of the bi-polar oceanic seesaw. Consequently, it appears that AIS melting strongly interacts with climate and ocean circulation globally. It is therefore necessary to account for this coupling in future climate and sea-level rise scenarios. Copyright 2008 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Atmospherics; Carbon dioxide; Control theory; Feedback; Glaciers; Global warming; Melting; Oceanography; Three dimensional; Antarctic bottom waters; Antarctic ices; Atlantic Meridional Overturning circulations; Climate models; Future climates; Ice covers; Local surfaces; Negative feedbacks; Ocean circulations; Polar ice sheets; Sea-level; Southern hemispheres; Southern oceans; Surface albedos; Time scales; Ice; albedo; climate change; climate modeling; global warming; halocline; ice cover; ice sheet; melting; sea ice; sea level change; Southern Hemisphere; three-dimensional modeling; Antarctica; Southern Ocean",,,,,,"Alley, R.B., Ice sheet and sea-level changes (2005) Science, 310, pp. 456-460; Bates, M.L., England, M.H., Sijp, W.P., On the multi-century Southern Hemisphere response to changes in atmospheric CO2-concentration in a global climate model (2005) Meteorol. Atmos. Phys, 89, pp. 17-36; Bi, D., Budd, W.F., Hirst, A.C., Wu, X., Collapse and reorganisation of the Southern Ocean overturning under global warming in a coupled model (2001) Geophys. Res. Lett, 28, pp. 3927-3930; Brix, H., Gerdes, R., North Atlantic Deep Water and Antarctic Bottom Water: Their interaction and influence on the variability of the global ocean circulation (2003) J. Geophys. Res, 108 (C2), p. 3022. , doi:10.1029/2002JC001335; Clark, P.U., Sea-level fingerprinting as a direct test for the source of global meltwater pulse IA (2002) Science, 295, pp. 2438-2441; 